1
00:00:04,394 --> 00:00:07,316
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur, 
Saraswatī Ṭhākur is quoting him saying,

2
00:00:07,316 --> 00:00:10,464
“The pastimes of Kṛṣṇa 
are not historical occurrences,

3
00:00:10,464 --> 00:00:12,425
and neither are they imaginary.”

4
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:15,732
[RealTime LiveStreaming Lila]

5
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:17,510
Prakaṭ, aprakaṭ.

6
00:00:17,510 --> 00:00:20,008
They’re manifested in this plane 
for sometime,

7
00:00:20,008 --> 00:00:21,331
and un-manifested.

8
00:00:21,331 --> 00:00:25,895
But you know, 
“Rāḍha−Kṛṣṇa nitya-līlā korilā prakāśha.”

9
00:00:25,895 --> 00:00:30,796
They’re eternal and cyclical 
and circular in nature.

10
00:00:32,538 --> 00:00:35,104
So, advanced devotees,

11
00:00:35,611 --> 00:00:39,847
they can penetrate 
into the depths of those pastimes.

12
00:00:39,847 --> 00:00:43,386
Chaitanya-charitāmṛtam 
is a living scripture.

13
00:00:44,187 --> 00:00:47,180
So, if someone is 
in a proper mood of devotion

14
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:50,306
when they’re hearing 
those pastimes,

15
00:00:50,306 --> 00:00:55,542
it’s real-time 
live streaming of Gaura-līlā.

16
00:00:56,327 --> 00:00:59,668
You’re not reading about 
what happened 500 years ago;

17
00:00:59,668 --> 00:01:02,931
you’re reading about 
what is happening.

18
00:01:02,931 --> 00:01:08,106
It’s happening somewhere 
at this moment. It’s going on.

19
00:01:08,106 --> 00:01:11,576
As Kavirāj Goswāmī says, 
and Guru Mahārāj is saying,

20
00:01:11,721 --> 00:01:14,765
“Evolution means 
gradual expression.”

21
00:01:14,765 --> 00:01:19,878
The sun, it has a position,
a fixed position, apparently.

22
00:01:20,679 --> 00:01:23,756
And we see, 
according to our relative position:

23
00:01:23,756 --> 00:01:29,532
the sun is rising, it’s noon, 
the sun is setting, it’s midnight.

24
00:01:30,862 --> 00:01:33,490
But if we did a conference call

25
00:01:33,490 --> 00:01:35,584
with people in different locations 
in the world

26
00:01:35,584 --> 00:01:38,983
simultaneously, 
and we said, “What do you see?”

27
00:01:38,983 --> 00:01:41,531
“Oh, I see 
the most beautiful sunrise.

28
00:01:41,531 --> 00:01:42,357
What do you see?”

29
00:01:42,357 --> 00:01:44,775
“Oh, I’m seeing 
an incredible sunset.

30
00:01:44,775 --> 00:01:45,522
What are you seeing?”

31
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:47,506
“No sun at all, 
it’s midnight.

32
00:01:47,506 --> 00:01:48,357
What are you seeing?”

33
00:01:48,357 --> 00:01:51,344
“The hot blazing sun 
overhead.”

34
00:01:51,913 --> 00:01:54,386
All simultaneously.

35
00:01:54,755 --> 00:02:02,355
So all the pastimes: 
the birth pastimes; the baby pastimes;

36
00:02:02,355 --> 00:02:06,392
childhood pastimes; Nanda−Yaśodā;

37
00:02:07,498 --> 00:02:10,441
Śrīdhām-sudhām (cowherd boys);

38
00:02:10,441 --> 00:02:13,896
then Vraja-gopīs; 
then to Mathurā, Dvārakā …

39
00:02:13,896 --> 00:02:16,467
It’s going in a circular way.

40
00:02:17,022 --> 00:02:21,842
So the devotees, 
what they’re remembering

41
00:02:23,436 --> 00:02:26,584
is not what is ‘past’ 
in this sense.

42
00:02:27,187 --> 00:02:29,913
It may take the shape 
of that sometimes,

43
00:02:29,913 --> 00:02:34,824
but really they live 
in the eternal present.

